chargeHist.descr: Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal)

result.execSummary:
The defendant Amber M Tuckwab was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
No possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Amber M Tuckwab in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:00 PM. Called 16CM85, 16CF33 and 16CF131. 16CF33 is SEHR and other two matters are PLEAS. State - 16CM85 - plead g/nc to counts #2 and #3 as alleged, counts #1 and #4 - DRI, joint recommendnation of 30 days jail on both counts #2 and #3 -  concurrent to each other, court costs on each count. State - 16CF131 - plead G to counts #2, #3, #6 and#7 as alleged, counts #1, #4 and #5 - DRI, joint recommendation on counts #2, #6 and #7 - 120 days jail on each count - concurrent to each other and to jail time on 16CM85, court costs on each count, on count #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years - consecutive to all jail times, with conditons of $300 fine plus costs, AODA and follow thru, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, employment/school, 200 hours of community service. Joy and Tuckwab agree. Court explains DRI to defendant. Court - 16CM85 - dismisses and reads in counts #1 and #4. Tuckwab pleads G to counts #2 and #3 on 16CM85; Court - 16CF131 - dismiss and reads in counts #1, #4 and #5. Tuckwab pleads G to counts #2, #3, #6 and #7 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts pleas, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Joy makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Tuckwab withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 16CM85 - counts #2 and #3 - 30 days in FC jail - concurrent to each other - huber and good time allowed - credit from 8/3/16 (credit for 30 days), court costs on each count - due 60 days after release from custody/CO (should be released today); 16CF131 - counts #2, #6 and #7 - 120 days in FC jail on each count - concurrent to each other and to jail on 16CM85 - huber and good time allowed - credit from 6/19/16 (credit for 120 days); court costs on each count - due 60 days after release from custody/CO (should be released today); count #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years - consecutive to jail time on 16CM85 and other counts on 16CF131 - with conditions of: $300 fine plus costs - 60 days after release from incarceration/CO (should be released today), AODA and follow thru, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 200 hours of community service - to be performed within the first year of probation, submit DNA sample, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, right to appeal. 16CF33 - both counsel have sentencing after revocation paperwork, no inaccuracies. State makes final argument prior to recommendations - recommends on both counts (#2 and #3) - 164 days credit. Joy makes final argument prior to recommendations - recommends 164 days on both counts. Tuckwab withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following - both counts #2 and #3 - 164 days jail on each count, concurrent to each other and concurrent to jail time imposed on 16CF131 and 16CM85, with 164 days credit, turn any unpaid fines into civil judgments, right to appeal, adjourned.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Amber M Tuckwab in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:30 AM. State - resolved - plead g/nc to counts #1, #2 as allged and amend count #3 to WI statute contrary to 450.11(7)(h) and amending repeater allegation to  939.62(1)(a) and then plead g/nc to amended count #3, #4 - DRI, #1 - DEJ for 6 months. #2 and #3 - probation for 2 years, court costs on each count, AODA and follow thru, absolute sobriety, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars, taverns and similar class B establishments, employment/school, 100 hours of community service. Voorhees agrees but has question in regards to count #1 - repeater allegation and thought that was to be deleted. State agrees. Voorhees provides court with plea questionnaire. Court amends count #1 to delete repeater allegations, Tuckwab pleads NC to count #1 as amended. Tuckwab pleads NC to count #2 as alleged. Court amends count #3 to possession of a prescription drug without a valid prescription contrary to 450.11(7)(h) - reads new charge and penalty and also amends the repeater allegation contrary to 939.62(1)(a). Tuckwab pleads NC to amended count #3. Court dismisses and reads in count #4. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty on counts #2 and #3 but withholds finding of guilt on count #1 and accepts DEJ for 6 months. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Voorhees makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Tuckwab withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #2 and #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years, concurrent to each other, with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, 100 hours of community service, costs on each count - paid thru probation, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, Court accepts DEJ for 6 months on count #1, submit DNA sample with expungement rights given, credit for 1 day only if revoked (stipulated), right to appeal, adjourned.
Final pre-trial on April 20, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
